1. English Version

1.1 Physiological Continuum Modeling

Biological tissues are modeled as nonlinear, anisotropic, and viscoelastic continua governed by the balance of mass, momentum, and energy. The fundamental equilibrium relation is expressed as:

\nabla \cdot \sigma + f = \rho \ddot{u}

where

 = Cauchy stress tensor

 = body force vector

 = tissue density

 = displacement field


Soft tissue mechanics incorporate hyperelastic constitutive relations such as:

\sigma = \frac{\partial W}{\partial \varepsilon}

with  being the strain energy density and  the Green-Lagrange strain tensor.

Boundary conditions include:

u = u_0 \quad \text{on } \Gamma_u

\sigma \cdot n = t_0 \quad \text{on } \Gamma_t î€

This provides a clinically interpretable representation of tissue deformation under physiological loading.


---

1.2 Organ-Level Multi-Physics Coupling

Organs are governed by coupled fields:

electro-mechanical coupling (e.g., heart)

fluidâ€“structure interaction (e.g., vessels, lungs)

transport and diffusion (e.g., liver, kidneys)

neural propagation dynamics (e.g., brain)


General transport behavior follows:

\frac{\partial c}{\partial t}
= D\nabla^2 c - v\cdot\nabla c + R(c)

representing concentration , diffusion , velocity , and reaction kinetics .


---

1.3 Finite Element Discretization

FEM converts PDEs into algebraic systems:

K(U)U = F

where

 = stiffness matrix

 = nodal unknowns

 = load vector


With nonlinear solvers via:

U^{(k+1)} = U^{(k)} + \Delta U

using Newtonâ€“Raphson iteration.


---
1.4 Physiological Regulation as Dynamic Control

Homeostasis is modeled as a closed-loop regulatory system:

x_{t+1} = f(x_t, u_t, p)

y_t = g(x_t) î€

where

 = physiological state vector

 = regulatory control inputs

 = biological parameters

 = measurable outputs


This forms the mathematical bridge to the AI Controller.


---

1.5 Explainable AI Controller

The controller learns mappings:

u_t = \pi_\theta(x_t)

subject to medical safety constraints:

h(u_t, x_t) \le 0

Optimization follows:

\min_{\theta}
\sum_t L(y_t, \hat{y}_t)
+ \lambda R(\theta)

Key properties:

âœ” parameter-controlled
âœ” interpretable
âœ” safety-bounded
âœ” auditable

This establishes a medically robust AI-governed multi-organ system.


