\begin{abstract}
The Medical AIâ€“FEM Unified Platform integrates finiteâ€“element multiphysics modeling with clinically interpretable AIâ€“based control. 
The system provides validated physiological simulations across major organ systems while maintaining transparency, safety, traceability, and medicalâ€“grade reproducibility. 
This paper presents the governing mathematics, numerical formulation, validation strategy, safety framework, and clinical relevance.
\end{abstract}

\section{Introduction}
Modern clinical research increasingly requires mechanistic physiological models that retain interpretability while leveraging dataâ€“driven learning. 
Traditional FEM solvers lack adaptive intelligence, while purely AIâ€“based models lack physical grounding.
The Medical AIâ€“FEM Core bridges these domains through a unified, safetyâ€“centered framework.

\section{Mathematical Framework}
\subsection{General FEM Formulation}
The structural dynamics problem is defined as:
\[
M \ddot{u} + C \dot{u} + K u = f
\]

where:
\begin{itemize}
\item $M$ â€“ mass matrix
\item $C$ â€“ damping matrix
\item $K$ â€“ stiffness matrix
\item $u$ â€“ displacement vector
\item $f$ â€“ external loading
\end{itemize}

The weak form is obtained via:
\[
\int_{\Omega} \sigma : \delta \epsilon \, d\Omega
=
\int_{\Omega} f \cdot \delta u \, d\Omega
+
\int_{\Gamma_t} t \cdot \delta u \, d\Gamma
\]

\subsection{Multiphysics Coupling}
Physiology requires coupling:
\[
\mathcal{F} =
\begin{bmatrix}
\text{solid mechanics}\\
\text{fluid dynamics}\\
\text{electrophysiology}\\
\text{biochemical transport}
\end{bmatrix}
\]

with timeâ€“resolved interaction constraints.

\section{AIâ€“Controller Formulation}
The AI controller adaptively tunes boundary and constitutive parameters while respecting safety constraints.

Objective:
\[
\min_{\theta}
\mathbb{E}
\| y_{sim}(\theta) - y_{clin} \|
\]

Subject to:
\[
\theta \in \mathcal{S}_{safe}
\]

where $\mathcal{S}_{safe}$ is a medically verified admissible set.

\section{Validation Strategy}
\subsection{Numerical Verification}
Mesh refinement is applied:

\[
E(h) \rightarrow 0 \quad \text{as } h\rightarrow 0
\]

\subsection{Physiological Validation}
Outputs are compared to clinical norms.

